Governor Seyi Makinde of Oyo State, on Sunday congratulated Senator Ademola Adeleke of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) on his victory in the Saturday governorship election in Osun State, defeating incumbent Governor Gboyega Oyetola of the All Progressives Congress. Governor Makinde expressed joy that a second PDP governor has emerged in southwest Nigeria.
Governor Makinde on his official twitter handle Seyi Makinde @seyiamakinde wrote: “On behalf of the government and the good people of Oyo State, I congratulate the Governor-Elect, Senator  @AAdeleke_01
and the people of Osun State on this victory. It’s great to have a second @OfficialPDPNig
flag flying in the southwest. Truly, power resides with the people.”
 
 
